HEADWORD: Comer
<hw>Com"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who comes, or who
has come; one who has arrived, and is present.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>All comers</b></col>, <cd>all who come, or offer, to take
part in a matter, especially in a contest or controversy.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧To
prove it against <xex>all comers</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comes</ent>⟦br⟧
